[thinking] **Clarifying class naming rules**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about how inner class names in bytecode have a $ symbol, while there's a rule against using $ in test class or file names. It seems a bit tricky because the inner classes compile with that $ sign, but the naming rule applies to the actual test class or file names. I need to sort this out to make sure I'm following the guidelines correctly. It feels confusing, and I want to get it right!
